# Firmware downloads

## OpenWRT firmware

To choose the firmware, look into the
[table of hardware](http://wiki.openwrt.org/toh/start) on the OpenWRT
site, each device page will list which firmware you should use.

Right after flashing, to ensure that tftp is available in case your router gets bricked, type these commands out in telnet/ssh:

    nvram set boot_wait=on
    nvram set boot_time=10
    nvram commit && reboot
    
(!) Note: On WRT54GL (at least), you should probably use 'wait_time' instead of 'boot_time'.

